    "created_at": "2016-01-11T06:25:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-11T06:25:29Z",
    "body": "`overlayScrollbar` is turned on by default when it is enabled in system, in your case I think it is because your system settings disabled overlay scrollbar.\n\nIf you still want to force turning it on, you can use the new `blinkFeatures` option:\n\n``` js\nnew BrowserWindow({\n  webPreferences: {\n    blinkFeatures: 'OverlayScrollbars'\n  }\n});\n```\n\nI didn't know people are actually using this option, sorry for breaking this.\n"
